It seems there is a serious bug in the QuotaEnforcer module. Redirects (e.g. 302) are not counted so sites with a lot of redirects go way beyond the specified limit. &lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
I have seen over 800Mb from a single host with a 10Mb limit&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Its the same weather the QuotaEnforcer is the first or last module in the processor chain&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Are redirects treated in a special way that never gets their content size summed up with all other URIs ?&lt;BR&gt;
